    "Colour-colour diagrams for KiDS DR5 sources.",
    "The stellar locus can be identified by the distinct clouds of data that are coincident with both SDSS stars (black contours) and Pickles stellar templates (pink dots).effects, visible by the consistent degradation of quality in all KiDZ fields.We find photo-z biases at the few percent level over all magnitudes, but which exacerbate at the extremes in photo-z (µ ∆z > 0.05) and redshift (µ ∆z < -0.05).",
    "These biases are typically accompanied by an increase in photo-z scatter, shown in the second row of the figure.",
    "Beyond spectroscopic and photometric redshifts (i.e.",
    "at z B ≥ 1 and z spec ≥ 1), the scatter in the photo-z can be seen to deteriorate for all available surveys due to the increased photometric noise of these distant objects."
